&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Posts 1 and 2: Senior Clinical Fellow in Hepatology and Liver Transplantation, fixed term 1 year beginning 1st March 2021&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The appointees will participate in the full range of daytime activities, to include general hepatology and specialist outpatients, endoscopy lists, contribution to care of Hepatology and Liver Transplant inpatients, research, audit and teaching. The appointees will be able to attend weekly MDTs scheduled in transplantation, viral hepatology and hepatobiliary malignancies, radiology and pathology meetings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The posts will be most suited to those reaching the end of their specialist training in gastroenterology/ hepatology wishing to gain more in-depth experience. As well as liver transplantation, there is opportunity to pursue a sub-specialist interest, for example, in acute-on-chronic liver failure, viral hepatitis, complex portal hypertension, autoimmune liver diseases, hepatocellular carcinoma or non-invasive fibrosis assessment. Participation in research is encouraged. An individualised programme of clinical sessions, research and audit will be agreed with the successful candidates to meet subspecialist interest and training needs. The post includes a contribution to the out-of-hours rota.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Dr Aileen Marshall&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Clinical Lead Hepatology &amp; Liver Transplant&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: aileen.marshall@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 020 3758 2000 extension: 31142 / 31624&lt;/p&gt;
